
Day 8 

Conditional formating

	normally a program will always execute from top to bottom unless stated otherwise by the programmer

	If

		How to format an if statement

			if ( enter your condition here ) {

				//in here go your commands or expressions
				}


	example of If Else statement:
		start --> ask user input score --> 
			If score < 60
				print --> pass
			Else 
				print --> fail

		multi branch IF

			start --> ask user input -->

			if (score > 90) 
				print --> "grade A" --> end statement

			else if (score > 80) 
				print --> "grade B" --> end statement

			else if (score > 70)
				print --> "grade C" --> end statement 

			else 
				print --> "keep trying" -- > end statement

		if WITHOUT ELSE
			Start --> ask user input -->
				if score < 60 
					mark fail
				NO ELSE
					enter score --> move on with program

